Turkeyâ€™s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  ended the day lower, down 0.7 percent to 51,747.43.  The following were among the active stocks on the Turkish
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Arcelik AS (ARCLK)  , the biggest maker of home
appliances, climbed 1 percent to 5.88 liras, in a second day of
gains. Arcelik, which is owned by  Koc Holding AS (KCHOL)  , may
take part in a government project to manufacture tablet
computers for school children, Hurriyet reported, citing Chief
Executive Levent Cakiroglu.  Yunsa Yunlu Sanayi & Ticaret AS (YUNSA TI), a woolen
fabrics maker owned by  Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL)  ,
gained 3.2 percent to 3.60 liras, the biggest increase in a
week. Yunsa plans to grow in  Brazil , China, Japan and Korea to
increase sales by 20 percent next year, Dunya reported, citing
Chief Executive Cem Celikoglu.  To contact the reporter on this story:
